               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-193v: Praises of God, Wǝddase Amlak, ውዳሴ፡ አምላክ፡. Devotional groups of prayers by Church Fathers, arranged for the days of the week. AbbCat 198, <locus target="#1r"/>, Notice 99; EMML 1432. Compilations of Prayers and Supplications for the Seven Days, ጸሎት ወስእለት እንተ ዘ፯ ዕለታት. F<locus target="#1r"/>-23v: Compilation of Prayers for Monday by Basil. F<locus target="#23v"/>-60r: Compilation of Prayers for Tuesday by Ephrem. F<locus target="#60r"/>-85v: Compilation of Prayers for Wednesday by Mari Ephrem. F<locus target="#86r"/>-119r: Compilation of Prayers for Thursday by Aragawi Manfas Qeddus. F<locus target="#119r"/>-146r: Compilation of Prayers for Friday by Synoda. F<locus target="#146r"/>-167r: Compilation of Prayers for Saturday by Athanatius of Egypt. F<locus target="#167v"/>-192v: Compilation of Prayers for Sunday by Cyril. Varia.  F. i v: Repetitive prayer. Notes. The book bears the seal of ownership (in blue ink) of አባ ዮሐንስ ጳጳስ ዘአክሱም ወዘቍሎን እድያማተ ትግራይ,  Abba Yohannes Bishop of Axum and all surrounding Tigre. <locus target="#193v"/> contains a colophon which gives the date from the creation of the world, the EC date, and in the 12th year of the reign of ፋሲለደስ, Fasiledas (1632-1667), whose regnal name is Seltan Segad. "ዘተሰምየ ስመ መንግስቱ ስልጣን ስገድ".</summary>
